<NEW>

Shaking his head RODIMUS said, "Nothing." He looked at the work
PERCEPTOR had done. "Good. Let's check out those caves."

RODIMUS PRIMAL'S chest plate lit up illuminating the tunnel. It looks
as if it was a mineshaft leading down into the mountain itself. Ahead
of them sensors could begin to pick up the faint readings of radiation
. . . the same kind of radiation that the humans had been throwing
into the statue the last time PERCEPTOR and WINDLORD had watched them
the first time.

"Be careful." RODIMUS said. "We don't know what's down here."

*     *     *    *    *

Meanwhile at the entrance of the cave a dark shadow moved and watched.
"They have come back and brought friends." A voice whispered into a
radio. "Get ready."

(TAG)

- Preston
